Totopos Con Chile
  --Gonzalo Guzman (Nopalito)

Salsa de Arbol:
1 tbsp olive oil
1/4 c dried arbol chiles, stemmed and seeded
1 1/2 c (12 oz) canned diced tomatoes and their juices
1 small tomatillo
2 tbsp white vinegar
1 small garlic clove
1/2 tsp kosher salt + more to taste

In a small pot, heat the oil over high heat, then add the chiles; let cook, continuously tossing the chiles so taht they do not burm ~ 10 s. When they turn bright orange, they are done. Immediately remove from the oil. Add 3/4 of the chiles to a blender and reserve the rest. Add the tomatoes, tomatillos, vinegra, garlic, salt, and 2 tbsp water, and blend until smooth. Taste and adjust the seasoning, or blend in more of the remaining chiles to taste. Pour into a small pot, bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and let simmer for 15 min. Server warm or cool.

Totopos:
2 c salsa de arbol
16 oz homemade salted corn tortilla chips, or thick, hearty store bought
1 c grated cotija cheese
1/2 c finely diced white onion
1/2 c fresh cilantro leaves, finely chopped
1 c crema or sour cream
lime wedges, for serving

Preheat oven to 450F. Spread chips on a baking sheet and bake until warmed through, ~2 min. Transfer chips to a large mixing bowl. Add the hot salsa and toss the chips until they are completely covered. transfer to a serving plate, then garnish with cheese, onions, and cilantro. Serve with the crema and lime wedges.

